AB  - In this note we revisit the empirical results in Bianchi, Büchner, and Tamoni (2020) after correcting for using information not available at the time the forecast was made. Although we note a decrease in out-of-sample $R^2$, the revised analysis confirms that bond excess return predictability from neural networks remains statistically and economically significant.
