TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jenter, Dirk
AU  - Lewellen, Katharina
T1  - Performance-Induced CEO Turnover
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa069
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 2
SP  - 569
EP  - 617
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper revisits the relationship between firm performance and CEO turnover. Instead of classifying turnovers into forced and voluntary, we introduce performance-induced turnover, defined as turnover that would not have occurred had performance been “good.” We document a close turnover-performance link and estimate that 38%–55% of turnovers are performance induced. This is significantly more than the number of forced turnovers, though the two types of turnovers are highly correlated. Compared to the predictions of Bayesian learning models, learning about CEO ability appears to be slow, and boards act as if CEO ability (or match quality) was subject to frequent shocks.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa069
ER  - 



